Class ThreadPoolMXBeanAdapter

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.ignite.internal.ThreadPoolMXBeanAdapter
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ThreadPoolMXBean

    public class ThreadPoolMXBeanAdapter
extends Object
implements ThreadPoolMXBean
    Adapter for ThreadPoolMXBean which delegates all method calls to the underlying ExecutorService instance.

        public boolean isTerminated()
        Returns true if all tasks have completed following shut down. Note that isTerminated() is never true unless either shutdown() or shutdownNow() was called first.
        Specified by:
        isTerminated in interface ThreadPoolMXBean

      • isTerminating

        public boolean isTerminating()
        Returns true if this executor is in the process of terminating after shutdown() or shutdownNow() but has not completely terminated. This method may be useful for debugging. A return of true reported a sufficient period after shutdown may indicate that submitted tasks have ignored or suppressed interruption, causing this executor not to properly terminate.
        Specified by:
        isTerminating in interface ThreadPoolMXBean
        Returns:
        True if terminating but not yet terminated.
